      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>black</strong> and<strong> white sesame seeds</strong>, crack your<strong> egg[s]</strong> into the pan and cook, covered, for 2 min or until done to your liking – this is your <strong>sesame fried egg</strong></p>",
